omy tag page URLs\n- Include feed.xml URL\n- URLs use baseUrl from config\n- Valid XML structure\n- Handle site with no tag pages\n\n### tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts (9 tests)\nTests for `createDevServerPlugin()`:\n- Store dev-server-config in ctx.data\n- Config includes port setting\n- Config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline\n- Config includes search index path\n- Config includes content routes\n- Default port is 3000\n- Handle missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n---\n\n## TASK.md Summary\n\n### Requirements\nBuild 8 plugins for `/workspace/src/plugins/` implementing the Plugin interface:\n\n**Wave 1 (no dependencies):**\n1. markdown-ext\n2. asset-pipeline\n3. syntax-highlight\n4. taxonomy\n\n**Wave 2 (depend on Wave 1):**\n5. rss-feed (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n6. search-index (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\n**Wave 3 (depend on Wave 2):**\n7. sitemap (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n8. dev-server (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n\nEach plugin must export a `createXxxPlugin()` factory function returning a Plugin object.\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Plugin Interface**: All plugins must implement the Plugin interface with name, version, dependencies, and hooks.\n\n2. **Hook System**: Three hook points:\n   - `beforeBuild`: Execute once before processing files\n   - `transformContent`: Transform each file individually\n   - `afterBuild`: Execute once after all files processed\n\n3. **Topological Sort**: BuildEngine uses depth-first search to resolve plugin execution order and detect circular dependencies.\n\n4. **Data Sharing**: Plugins communicate via `ctx.data` Map to pass information between plugins:\n   - `asset-manifest`: from asset-pipeline\n   - `taxonomy-tags`: from taxonomy\n   - `dev-server-config`: from dev-server\n\n5. **Factory Pattern**: Each plugin is created via a factory function (e.g., `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`).\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete codebase. The plugins directory is empty and nee